### Teko build artifacts ###
*.tkb
*.tkcov
# (0.3.0.30) a `.tkb` at the root of a regressive project is the authored BDD regression SPEC
# (the canonical format, docs/design/tkb-regression-format.md), NOT the build artifact the
# `*.tkb` rule above ignores — keep the authored specs tracked.
!examples/regressions/**/*.tkb
!examples/regression-fixture/**/*.tkb

### WASM test harness build output ###
*.wasm
*.wat
*.mjs
### Teko project build outputs (regenerated by `teko build`; never committed) ###
examples/**/*.c
examples/regressions/match_pattern_bindings/match_pattern_bindings
examples/regressions/optionals/optionals
examples/regressions/noncapturing_lambda_lift/noncapturing_lambda_lift

# native-backend build artifacts (teko build .)
/teko.c
/teko
/bin/
# native-build output dirs anywhere (teko build . -> <proj>/bin)
bin/
# (0.3.0.30 R2) the regression runner builds each curated/fixture regressive with `-o bin`
# relative to the regressive dir — keep those working trees clean so they never perturb the
# fixpoint / byte-identity checks. (Redundant with the global `bin/` above; named for the crumb.)
examples/regressions/**/bin/
examples/regression-fixture/**/bin/
# self-host verification output dirs (the gen1/gen2/gen3 byte-identity gate)
/gen1/
/gen2/
/gen3/
# dot-prefixed variants of the same gate dirs (.gen2/.gen3 — PR #100 committed them by accident)
.gen*/
cobertura.xml

# per-worktree downloaded teko compiler (scripts/fetch_teko.sh)
.teko/
# per-worktree PROVISIONED seed (scripts/ci_provision_teko.sh) + downloaded archives — NEVER commit a binary
.seed/
teko-*.tar.gz
teko-*.zip
gd-*/
/out/
# throwaway gen1 self-host build dir (teko build . -o gen1out)
/gen1out/
/.work/
/build/
/bin/

# native-build output dir (teko build -> <proj>/target for some layouts) — NEVER commit
target/
